This project formalises the powerset construction in Coq.

The formalisation contains basic definitions of words, languages, DFAs,
NFAs, acceptance semantics, the powerset construction, and a correctness
proof showing that the constructed DFA recognizes the same language as the
original NFA.

The main results are:

- words and languages
  (Definitions word and lang in AutomataBase.v);

- deterministic and nondeterministic finite automata
  (Records DFA and NFA in AutomataBase.v);

- acceptance semantics for DFAs and NFAs
  (Definitions dfa_accept and nfa_accept in AutomataSemantics.v);

- epsilon-closure for NFAs
  (Definition epsilon_closure in EpsilonClosure.v);

- the powerset construction from NFAs to DFAs
  (Definition nfa_to_dfa in PowersetConstruction.v);

- correctness of the powerset construction
  (Theorem nfa_to_dfa_correct in PowersetConstruction.v);

- finiteness of the constructed DFA state space
  (Record FiniteType, Lemma all_powerset_states_cover, and Theorem
  powerset_construction_preserves_finiteness in Finiteness.v).


This repository is still beings updated.

Please let me know if you find a mistake or have suggestions for improvement.